17 receipt requested, or email) on (date delivered, mailed, or emailed) __________ (date
18 delivered, mailed, or emailed)';"
19 "(5) Service of any document may be perfected either before or after filing such service
20 with the clerk. If service is made by certified mail or statutory overnight delivery, return
21 receipt requested, it shall be deemed perfected on the day it was deposited in the mail.
22 If service is perfected by certified mail or statutory overnight delivery, return receipt
23 requested, three days shall be added to any deadline required for a response, to allow for
24 mailing;
25 (6) If the address of any party is unknown and the party is not represented by an attorney
26 of record, service may be perfected on the party by certified mail or statutory overnight
27 delivery, return receipt requested, directed to the last known address of the party; and"
28 SECTION 2.
29 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
